  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2939",
  "title": " fix(connectInfiniteHits): fix #2928 ",
  "body": "When there is a slow network, the stalled search mechanics will trigger a new render with the same content. This has generally no impact. However the infinite builds up a list of all the results, and there was no mechanics in place to check if the same page has been already received.\r\n\r\nTo test, you can use dev-novel and with the performance set to slow 3g, you can see that there are no duplicates.\r\n\r\nFix #2928 \r\n\r\nMight also be a patch for #2938 (need confirmation)",
